Flagstone Estimates U.S. Storms May Lead to $30 Million in Costs

-- B y   B r o o k e   S u t h e r l a n d
-- 
2011-06-30T21:14:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/flagstone-estimates-u-s-storms-may-lead-to-30-million-in-costs.html
Flagstone Reinsurance Holdings SA (FSR) ,
the company formed in response to the 2005 hurricane season,
said U.S. storms in the quarter ended today will lead to costs
of $25 million to $30 million.  Revised estimates for catastrophes that occurred in the
first quarter will add an additional $20 million to $25 million
in costs for the current period, the Luxembourg-based company
said today in a statement distributed by Business Wire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brooke Sutherland in New York at 
 bsutherland5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  